Food Categories:  
There are 4 food categories: Meals, Snacks, Beverages and Desserts. 
 
Meals:  
Chicken Biryani: Chicken Biryani belongs to Meals category. Chicken Biryani costs Rs.130. It takes 20 
minutes to prepare Chicken Biriyani. Chicken Biriyani belongs to Non-Veg category. Chicken Biryani is 
a mixed rice dish, and there are many different versions of it that vary by region. The dish consists of 
basmati rice, spices and chicken. It is made all across the Indian subcontinent, as well as in the UK 
and other countries with large South Asian diasporas.    
The ingredients include: Chicken, rice, onion, garlic, ginger, garam masala, yogurt, and ghee (clarified 
butter). The spices used may include: bay leaves, coriander, mint, and chili peppers. The method of 
preparation is to marinate the chicken in the yogurt and spices, then cook it in a large pot with the 
rice and other ingredients. The dish is often garnished with fried onions and cilantro.

preparation is to marinate the chicken in the yogurt and spices, then cook it in a large pot with the 
rice and other ingredients. The dish is often garnished with fried onions and cilantro.  
 
Ingredients to make Chicken Biryani: 
1 pound chicken, cut into pieces 
1 cup basmati rice 
1/2 cup plain yogurt 
1/4 cup chopped onion 
1/4 cup chopped cilantro 
1/4 cup chopped mint 
1 tablespoon garam masala 
1 teaspoon salt 
1/2 teaspoon turmeric 
1/4 teaspoon chili powder 
1/4 cup ghee (clarified butter) 
 
Instructions to make Chicken Biryani:    
Marinate the chicken in the yogurt, garam masala, salt, turmeric, and chili powder for at least 30 
minutes. 
Heat the ghee in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened. 
Add the chicken and cook until browned on all sides.

Add the rice, cilantro, mint, and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and 
simmer for 20 minutes, or until the rice is cooked through. 
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. 
 
 
Fried Rice: Fried Rice belongs to Meals category. Fried Rice costs Rs.120. It takes 20 minutes to 
prepare Fried Rice. Fried rice belongs to Veg category. Fried rice is a beloved dish enjoyed across the 
globe, characterized by cooked rice that is stir-fried in a wok or frying pan, often mixed with other 
ingredients such as vegetables, eggs, meat, seafood, or a combination thereof. Its origins can be 
traced back to the Sui Dynasty in China, where it developed as a way to utilize leftover cooked rice, 
minimizing food waste. This resourceful beginning has led to countless variations, each reflecting 
regional tastes and available ingredients. The cooking process typically involves heating oil in a wok

regional tastes and available ingredients. The cooking process typically involves heating oil in a wok 
or pan over high heat, then adding aromatics like garlic, ginger, or onions to infuse the oil with 
flavor. The cooked rice, ideally day-old or chilled to prevent stickiness, is then added and stir-fried 
until heated through and slightly browned. Various seasonings and sauces, such as soy sauce, oyster 
sauce, fish sauce, or even ketchup in some regions, are incorporated to enhance the flavor profile. 
Common additions to fried rice include diced vegetables like carrots, peas, and onions, scrambled 
eggs, and proteins like chicken, pork, shrimp, or tofu. The versatility of fried rice is one of its greatest 
strengths; it can be adapted to suit vegetarian, vegan, or meat-lover preferences, and can 
incorporate a wide range of flavors from savory and spicy to sweet and tangy. From the simple egg

strengths; it can be adapted to suit vegetarian, vegan, or meat-lover preferences, and can 
incorporate a wide range of flavors from savory and spicy to sweet and tangy. From the simple egg 
fried rice to elaborate nasi goreng in Indonesia or arroz chaufa in Peru, fried rice stands as a 
testament to the culinary ingenuity of transforming humble ingredients into a satisfying and globally 
appreciated meal.  
 
Ingredients for Fried Rice: 
Cooked Rice: The most important ingredient! Ideally, use day-old rice that has been chilled. This 
prevents it from becoming mushy during stir-frying. Long-grain rice like Jasmine or Basmati works 
well. 
Oil: Use a high-heat oil like vegetable oil, canola oil, or peanut oil. 
Aromatics: 
Garlic, minced 
Ginger, minced (optional but recommended) 
Onion, diced (optional) 
Vegetables: You can use a variety of vegetables. Some common choices include: 
Carrots, diced 
Peas (fresh or frozen) 
Green beans, chopped 
Corn

Protein (optional): 
Eggs, lightly beaten 
Chicken, diced and cooked 
Pork, diced and cooked 
Shrimp, cooked 
Tofu, diced and pressed 
Sauces and Seasonings: 
Soy sauce 
Oyster sauce (optional) 
Sesame oil (optional) 
Salt and pepper 
 
Instructions to Make Fried Rice: 
Prepare the ingredients to make Fried rice: Cook the rice ahead of time and chill it. Chop all 
vegetables and protein into bite-sized pieces. Mince the garlic and ginger. If using eggs, lightly beat 
them in a bowl. 
Cook the eggs (if using): Heat a little oil in a wok or large frying pan over medium-high heat. Pour in 
the beaten eggs and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly scrambled. Remove the eggs from the 
pan and set aside. 
Stir-fry the aromatics and vegetables: Add more oil to the pan and heat over medium-high heat. Add 
the garlic, ginger, and onion (if using) and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant. Add the 
vegetables and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes until slightly softened.

the garlic, ginger, and onion (if using) and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant. Add the 
vegetables and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes until slightly softened. 
Add the rice: Add the cooked rice to the pan and break up any clumps with a spatula or spoon. Stir-
fry for 2-3 minutes until the rice is heated through. 
Add the protein (if using) and sauces: Add the cooked eggs (or other protein) back to the pan. Pour 
in the soy sauce and oyster sauce (if using) and stir well to combine. 
Season and finish: Drizzle with sesame oil (if using) and season with salt and pepper to taste. Stir-fry 
for another minute or two until everything is heated through and well combined. 
Serve hot: Serve the fried rice immediately. 
 
 
Chicken Burger: Fried Rice belongs to Meals category. Fried Rice costs Rs.120. It takes 15 minutes to 
prepare Chicken Burger. Chicken burger belongs to Non-Veg category. A chicken burger is a popular

prepare Chicken Burger. Chicken burger belongs to Non-Veg category. A chicken burger is a popular 
sandwich consisting of a cooked chicken patty served within a sliced bun, often accompanied by 
various toppings and condiments. The core ingredient, the chicken patty, is typically made from 
ground chicken, which is seasoned with spices like salt, pepper, garlic powder, and sometimes

paprika or other herbs, then mixed with breadcrumbs and an egg to bind the mixture. The patty can 
be cooked by grilling, pan-frying, baking, or deep-frying, resulting in variations in texture and flavor. 
Grilled or pan-fried patties tend to be leaner and have a more savory, slightly charred flavor, while 
deep-fried patties offer a crispy, golden-brown exterior. The taste of a chicken burger depends 
heavily on the seasonings used in the patty and the chosen toppings. Common additions include 
lettuce, tomato, onion, pickles, cheese (such as cheddar or American), and sauces like mayonnaise, 
ketchup, mustard, or specialized burger sauces. These toppings contribute to a balance of flavors 
and textures, with the crispness of lettuce and onion, the juiciness of tomato, the tang of pickles, 
and the richness of cheese and sauces complementing the savory chicken. The preparation involves 
mixing the ground chicken with seasonings and binding agents, forming the patties, cooking them

and the richness of cheese and sauces complementing the savory chicken. The preparation involves 
mixing the ground chicken with seasonings and binding agents, forming the patties, cooking them 
until fully cooked and browned, and then assembling the burger by placing the patty on a bun with 
the chosen toppings. The versatility of the chicken burger allows for countless variations, from 
simple versions with minimal toppings to gourmet creations with premium ingredients and unique 
flavor combinations, making it a globally enjoyed and adaptable meal. 
 
Ingredients to make Chicken Burger: 
 
For the Chicken Patties: 
1 pound ground chicken    
1/2 cup breadcrumbs (panko or regular)    
1/4 cup finely chopped onion 
1 egg, lightly beaten    
1-2 cloves garlic, minced    
1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce (optional, for extra flavor) 
1 teaspoon salt 
1/2 teaspoon black pepper 
1/2 teaspoon paprika 
1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 
1 tablespoon olive oil (for cooking)

1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce (optional, for extra flavor) 
1 teaspoon salt 
1/2 teaspoon black pepper 
1/2 teaspoon paprika 
1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 
1 tablespoon olive oil (for cooking)    
For the Burger Assembly: 
4 burger buns    
Lettuce leaves 
Tomato slices    
Onion slices (red or white) 
Pickles (optional)    
Cheese slices (cheddar, American, or your favorite)

Condiments of your choice (mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard, burger sauce) 
 
Instructions to make Chicken Burger: 
Prepare the Chicken Patty Mixture: 
In a large bowl, combine the ground chicken, breadcrumbs, chopped onion, egg, minced garlic, 
Worcestershire sauce (if using), salt, pepper, paprika, and garlic powder. 
Gently mix all the ingredients together until just combined. Be careful not to overmix, as this can 
make the patties tough. 
Form the Patties: 
Divide the chicken mixture into 4 equal portions. 
Shape each portion into a patty about 3/4 inch thick. Make a small indentation in the center of each 
patty with your thumb; this helps them cook evenly and prevents them from bulging in the middle.    
Cook the Patties: 
Heat the olive oil in a large skillet or grill pan over medium heat.    
Carefully place the chicken patties in the hot skillet or on the grill. 
Cook for about 5-6 minutes per side, or until the patties are cooked through and have reached an

Carefully place the chicken patties in the hot skillet or on the grill. 
Cook for about 5-6 minutes per side, or until the patties are cooked through and have reached an 
internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). The patties should be nicely browned on the outside and no 
longer pink inside. 
If using cheese, place a slice on each patty during the last minute of cooking to allow it to melt. 
Toast the Buns (Optional): 
While the patties are cooking, you can lightly toast the cut sides of the burger buns in a dry skillet or 
toaster for a few minutes until lightly golden. This adds a nice texture to the burger.    
Assemble the Burgers: 
Spread your desired condiments on the top and bottom buns. 
Place a cooked chicken patty on the bottom bun. 
Add your desired toppings, such as lettuce, tomato slices, onion slices, and pickles. 
Top with the other bun and serve immediately.

Pasta Alfredo: Pasta Alfredo belongs to Meals category. Pasta Alfredo costs Rs.150. It takes 20 
minutes to prepare Pasta Alfredo. Pasta Alfredo belongs to Veg category. Pasta Alfredo is a classic 
Italian-American pasta dish characterized by its rich, creamy, and cheesy sauce. The traditional, and 
simpler, Roman version, pasta al burro, consists solely of pasta tossed with butter and Parmesan

cheese. The Americanized version, which is what we generally know as Alfredo, is a richer 
adaptation featuring heavy cream or double cream added to the butter and Parmesan, creating a 
luxurious and coating sauce. The ingredients are relatively few but crucial: good quality butter 
(preferably unsalted), heavy cream, freshly grated Parmesan cheese (Parmigiano-Reggiano is ideal), 
and black pepper. The preparation involves cooking the pasta (usually fettuccine, but other long 
pasta shapes like tagliatelle or linguine work well) until al dente. 2  While the pasta cooks, the sauce 
is made by melting butter in a pan, then gradually whisking in the heavy cream until it thickens 
slightly. Freshly grated Parmesan cheese is then added and stirred until it melts and creates a 
smooth, emulsified sauce. 1  The cooked pasta is then added directly to the pan with the sauce and 
tossed vigorously to ensure every strand is coated. 3  A generous grind of black pepper is added for a

tossed vigorously to ensure every strand is coated. 3  A generous grind of black pepper is added for a 
touch of spice and to balance the richness. The taste of Pasta Alfredo is intensely creamy, buttery, 
and cheesy, with a savory umami depth from the Parmesan. It's a comforting and indulgent dish, 
best served immediately while the sauce is still warm and smooth. While variations exist, such as 
adding garlic, chicken, or other ingredients, the classic Alfredo is appreciated for its simplicity and 
the harmonious blend of its core components.  
 
 
 
Veg Thali: Veg Thali belongs to Meals category. Veg Thali costs Rs.140. It takes 20 minutes to prepare 
Veg Thali. Veg Thali belongs to Veg category. A Veg Thali, meaning "plate" in Hindi, is a complete and 
balanced Indian meal served on a large platter, offering a diverse array of vegetarian dishes designed 
to provide a satisfying and wholesome dining experience. It's a popular way to sample various

balanced Indian meal served on a large platter, offering a diverse array of vegetarian dishes designed 
to provide a satisfying and wholesome dining experience. It's a popular way to sample various 
regional cuisines and flavors in one sitting. A typical Veg Thali includes a selection of curries, such as 
dal (lentil soup), vegetable curries (like mixed vegetables, paneer (Indian cheese), or potato-based 
dishes), a dry vegetable preparation (like a stir-fry), rice (usually plain or jeera rice), roti (flatbread 
like chapati or naan), yogurt or raita (a yogurt-based condiment), a small portion of sweet dish (like 
gulab jamun or kheer), and sometimes papad (thin, crispy lentil wafers) and pickles. The ingredients 
used vary greatly depending on the region and specific dishes included, but common staples include 
lentils, various vegetables (potatoes, cauliflower, peas, spinach, etc.), spices (turmeric, cumin,

used vary greatly depending on the region and specific dishes included, but common staples include 
lentils, various vegetables (potatoes, cauliflower, peas, spinach, etc.), spices (turmeric, cumin, 
coriander, garam masala, etc.), dairy products (milk, yogurt, ghee), and different types of flours for 
the breads. The taste profile of a Veg Thali is complex and layered, offering a balance of sweet, salty, 
spicy, tangy, and sometimes bitter notes. The curries provide rich, flavorful sauces, the rice and roti 
offer a neutral base, the yogurt provides a cooling element, and the sweet dish offers a satisfying 
finish. Preparation involves cooking each dish separately, often using different cooking methods like 
simmering, stir-frying, and baking. The thali is then carefully arranged on the platter, with each dish 
placed in a designated compartment or small bowl, creating a visually appealing and balanced meal 
that showcases the diversity and richness of Indian vegetarian cuisine.

Mutton Curry: Mutton Curry belongs to Meals category. Mutton Curry costs Rs.140. It takes 25 
minutes to prepare Mutton Curry. Mutton curry belongs to NonVeg category. Mutton curry is a rich

and flavorful dish popular across various cultures, particularly in South Asia, the Middle East, and the 
Caribbean. It features tender pieces of mutton (goat meat) simmered in a spiced gravy or sauce. 
The specific ingredients and preparation methods vary significantly by region, but some common 
elements remain. 2  The base of most mutton curries involves a blend of aromatic spices, often 
including ginger, garlic, onions, turmeric, cumin, coriander, chili powder (for heat), and garam 
masala (a blend of warming spices like cardamom, cloves, cinnamon, and black pepper). 2  Other 
frequently used ingredients include tomatoes (fresh or canned), yogurt (for tenderizing the meat 
and adding creaminess), and sometimes coconut milk or cream for richness. 3  The meat is typically 
marinated in a mixture of yogurt and spices before being browned in oil or ghee. 4  Then, a base of 
onions, ginger, and garlic is sautéed until golden brown, followed by the addition of ground spices

onions, ginger, and garlic is sautéed until golden brown, followed by the addition of ground spices 
and tomatoes. The marinated mutton is then added to the spice mixture and simmered slowly until 
tender, allowing the flavors to meld and deepen. 5  The taste of mutton curry ranges from mild and 
creamy to intensely spicy, depending on the specific spice blend and the amount of chili used. The 
meat itself becomes incredibly tender and absorbs the complex flavors of the gravy, resulting in a 
deeply satisfying and aromatic dish. Different regional variations may incorporate ingredients like 
potatoes, peas, or other vegetables, and some might use vinegar or tamarind for a tangy note. 
Whether it's a rich Rogan Josh from Kashmir, a spicy Vindaloo from Goa, or a creamy Mutton Korma, 
mutton curry is a testament to the art of slow cooking and the transformative power of spices.

Grilled Chicken: Grilled Chicken belongs to Meals category. Grilled Chicken costs Rs.180. It takes 25 
minutes to prepare Grilled Chicken. Grilled chicken belongs to Non-Veg category. Grilled Chicken is a 
universally popular dish featuring chicken cooked over direct heat, typically on a grill, though other 
methods like broiling or pan-grilling can achieve similar results. The preparation often begins with 
marinating the chicken in a flavorful mixture that can range from simple combinations of oil, lemon 
juice, herbs, and spices to more complex marinades incorporating ingredients like yogurt, soy sauce, 
or honey. This marination process not only infuses the chicken with flavor but also helps to tenderize 
it. The chicken, whether whole, halved, or in individual pieces like breasts, thighs, or drumsticks, is 
then placed on the preheated grill. The high heat sears the surface, creating attractive grill marks

then placed on the preheated grill. The high heat sears the surface, creating attractive grill marks 
and a slightly charred, smoky flavor, while the internal temperature rises until the chicken is cooked 
through. The taste of grilled chicken can vary widely depending on the marinade and seasonings 
used. It can be savory, smoky, spicy, sweet, or tangy. The texture is characterized by a slightly crispy 
exterior and a juicy, tender interior when cooked correctly. Overcooking can lead to dry, tough 
chicken, so careful monitoring of the internal temperature is crucial. Grilled chicken is a versatile 
dish that can be served on its own, used in salads, sandwiches, tacos, or as a component in more 
elaborate meals. Its relatively healthy cooking method, which minimizes the use of added fats, 
makes it a popular choice for those seeking a lighter yet satisfying meal.

Fish Curry: Fish Curry belongs to Meals category. Fish Curry costs Rs.150. It takes 20 minutes to 
prepare Fish Curry. Fish curry belongs to Non-Veg category. Fish Curry is a diverse and globally 
enjoyed dish featuring fish cooked in a sauce or gravy, with countless variations reflecting regional 
cuisines and available ingredients. The base of most fish curries is a flavorful sauce, which can range 
from creamy coconut milk-based gravies in South Asia and Southeast Asia to tangy tomato-based 
sauces in other parts of the world. Common ingredients contributing to the flavor profile include 
aromatics like onions, garlic, ginger, and chilies, along with a blend of spices such as turmeric, cumin, 
coriander, and garam masala. The type of fish used also varies greatly, from firm white fish like cod 
or haddock to oily fish like salmon or mackerel, each imparting its unique texture and taste to the

or haddock to oily fish like salmon or mackerel, each imparting its unique texture and taste to the 
curry. The preparation typically involves sautéing the aromatics in oil or ghee to release their flavors, 
followed by the addition of spices and other vegetables like tomatoes or bell peppers. The fish is 
then added to the simmering sauce and cooked until tender and flaky. Coconut milk is often added 
towards the end for richness and creaminess, while ingredients like tamarind, vinegar, or lemon 
juice provide a tangy counterpoint to the spices. The taste of fish curry can vary dramatically 
depending on the specific recipe, ranging from mild and subtly spiced to fiery hot and intensely 
flavorful. It's often served with rice, naan bread, or other flatbreads to soak up the delicious gravy. 
Fish curry is not only a tasty and satisfying meal but also a good source of protein and omega-3 fatty 
acids, making it a healthy and nutritious option.
